01:09:04.259 --> 01:09:05.259
daily is that social change isn't really exciting
to audiences at their core.

01:09:05.259 --> 01:09:06.259
What's exciting to people is conflict. But
obviously, I'm working with big brands and

01:09:06.259 --> 01:09:07.259
brands don't want to be associated with conflict.
So, what do you think about that?

01:09:07.259 --> 01:09:08.259
&gt;&gt;Susan Bonds: Well, I think that's--. I mean,
obviously lots of people are always coming

01:09:08.259 --> 01:09:11.949
to us saying, "How can we use this for good?"
And going back to where we were able to see

01:09:11.949 --> 01:09:16.480
in Year Zero, was you can't tell people what
to care about, but you can set up a construct

01:09:16.480 --> 01:09:19.199
through which they see the world through different
eyes.

01:09:19.199 --> 01:09:24.159
But you're really at a conflict yourself,
because you just pointed it out. 'Cause great

01:09:24.159 --> 01:09:29.969
storytelling has conflict. So, you can't really
put someone else in someone else's shoes unless

01:09:29.969 --> 01:09:35.449
you create that drama. So, I mean, I believe
in that entertainment, like we've seen it.

01:09:35.449 --> 01:09:39.559
There's a million examples we can point to,
films that made us think differently about

01:09:39.559 --> 01:09:44.200
the world or an issue or a situation. So,
I think that this media is as well. You have

01:09:44.200 --> 01:09:49.989
to stick true to good quality storytelling.
You have to put people in the world in the

01:09:49.989 --> 01:09:50.989
situation in the story.

01:09:50.989 --> 01:09:55.179
And you can't just expect them because it's
for good. You can't tell them what to care

01:09:55.179 --> 01:09:57.809
about. We can't tell you people what to care
about either. You know what I'm saying? It's

01:09:57.809 --> 01:10:02.170
like, "No, we're just gonna think for ourselves."
So what you can do is bring them into a world

01:10:02.170 --> 01:10:18.980
of story where they experience it personally
and it changes the way they see the world.

01:10:18.980 --> 01:10:32.610
That's my two cents.

01:10:32.610 --> 01:10:46.710
&gt;&gt;Paul Woolmington: Question in the back.

01:10:46.710 --> 01:10:55.050
&gt;&gt;MALE AUDIENCE MEMBER #2: [ inaudible; off
