01:12:28.070 --> 01:12:33.030
way for character generation and testing.
Had they had the business plans that they

01:12:33.030 --> 01:12:39.540
would become the big entertainment entities
that they are today, I don't know if anyone

01:12:39.540 --> 01:12:41.000
would've believed them.

01:12:41.000 --> 01:12:45.380
Like, "This is what we're going to do, is
publish on cheap pulp paper for 40 years and

01:12:45.380 --> 01:12:50.880
then we're going to make a hundred million
dollar celluloid things."

01:12:50.880 --> 01:12:51.880
[laughter]

01:12:51.880 --> 01:13:02.280
&gt;&gt;Paul Woolmington: Stan Lee, yeah. An interesting
observation I think is that--and I hate to

01:13:02.280 --> 01:13:07.989
plug another book--but there's a book by a
friend called Peter Sims and it's "Small Bets."

01:13:07.989 --> 01:13:12.599
And have a read of it. And I think it's just
interesting him talking a lot about small

01:13:12.599 --> 01:13:13.599
bets.

01:13:13.599 --> 01:13:20.320
We have this tendency in Hollywood and in
marketing and what's the big idea, you know?

01:13:20.320 --> 01:13:25.059
Everyone's looking for this big idea. And
actually, the greatest successes of today

01:13:25.059 --> 01:13:29.600
were these iterative successes where they
place small bets and they made mistakes and

01:13:29.600 --> 01:13:30.829
learnt by their mistakes.

01:13:30.829 --> 01:13:36.829
And that's the theory behind the book and
it's just this notion of how you experiment.

01:13:36.829 --> 01:13:41.920
You were talking a little bit about the loosening
yourself up into that experimentation mode,

01:13:41.920 --> 01:13:47.499
but I think we're gonna see so many more amazing
business plans come out of small bets and

01:13:47.499 --> 01:13:51.190
being able to lose, but lose small but learn
from it.

01:13:51.190 --> 01:13:52.750
I think that's interesting.

01:13:52.750 --> 01:13:57.260
&gt;&gt;Chris Di Cesare: Yeah, just to add on that,
I just think that that's the beauty of the

01:13:57.260 --> 01:14:02.961
web in the fact that costs are coming down.
